8. Methods Statement

DNA barcode sequences for Eubalaena were downloaded from the Barcode of Life Data System (BOLD; Ratnasingham & Hebert, 2007) and processed using BOLDGenotyper v1.0.0. A total of 61 sequences were analyzed after removing duplicates and filtering for sequence quality (minimum length: 400 bp). Sequences were aligned using MAFFT (Katoh & Standley, 2013) and trimmed with trimAl (Capella-Guti√©rrez et al., 2009). Consensus genotypes were identified through hierarchical clustering at 97% sequence identity using average linkage. Individual sequences were assigned to genotypes using edit distance calculations (minimum identity: 50%). Geographic distributions were mapped using coordinates provided in BOLD and assigned to ocean basins using the Global Oceans and Seas (GOaS) v1 dataset (Flanders Marine Institute, 2021). 61 sequences (100.0%) were successfully assigned to 1 consensus genotypes.
